messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full path
- /api/orders/mine

All methods acceptable
- false

HTTP methods accepted by the code (based only on the source)
- HEAD: false
- POST: false
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation (concise)
- server.js mounts the order routes at the prefix "/api/orders": app.use('/api/orders', orderRoutes).
- routes/orderRoutes.js defines router.route('/mine').get(protect, getMyOrders); so the getMyOrders handler is reachable at the combined path "/api/orders" + "/mine" → "/api/orders/mine", and it is registered only for HTTP GET.
- There is no router.route(...).all(...) or any handler registered for other HTTP verbs on "/mine", so only GET is accepted by the code.
- The code does not explicitly register a HEAD handler; per your instruction, we do not assume framework-provided behavior, so HEAD is marked false.
- The controller comment shows a different mnemonic path (GET /api/orders/myorders) but that is a comment mismatch — the actual route in code is '/mine' as shown above.
